rces" and services are listed as "Consumers." Connecting this data to the previously published ecological networks with species interactions (i.e., trophic, parasitism) forms a topological network with species and service nodes. We also provide a protocol for assigning services to ecological networks that can be used in other ecosystems. This dataset provides a step towards advancing knowledge of important supporting species for ecosystem services and developing new ecological network methods for ecosystem services. There are no copyright restrictions; please cite this data paper when the data are used in publications.
